HEADWORD: Waped
<hw>Waped</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E.
<ets>wape</ets> pale, v., to stupefy, akin to <ets>wap</ets> to beat.
Cf. <er>Whap</er>, and <er>Wappened</er>.]</ety> <def>Cast down; crushed
by misery; dejected.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

